title: ‘Selfish demonstrations’: The left are hijacking Australia Day
description: Indigenous leader Warren Mundine says the left hijacking events with protests show they are people who “hate this country”.  “Get on with the day of actually celebrating Australia,” Mr Mundine said.  “What the hell are these people … who want to get out there and hijack our day and hijack the Aboriginal issues for their own selfish hatred and their own selfish demonstrations.”

title: ABC’s ‘Always Was Tonight’ is ‘utter nonsense’: Mundine
description: Indigenous leader Warren Mundine says comments during ABC’s show ‘Always Was Tonight’ were “disgraceful”.  “Here we are, again, trying to build this country and bring people together and here he is, out there making allegations,” Mr Mundine said.  “The First Fleet … started biological warfare to kill and wipe out Aboriginal people.”

title: ‘Heartfelt’: AJAC Executive Manager accepts Albanese’s apology to Jewish Australians
description: AJAC Executive Manager Joel Burnie says the Jewish community accepts Prime Minister Anthony Albanese’s apology over the Bondi attack.  “I and the Jewish community and those in the audience do accept that,” Mr Burnie said.  “It may have taken a little bit longer … for what was the largest terror attack in Australia’s history but it was an incremental increase of an explosion of antisemitism over a two-year period on his and his colleagues’ watch.”

title: Antisemitic horror stories at Australian schools are ‘unsurprising’
description: AJAC Executive Manager Joel Burnie says antisemitic horror stories at Australian schools does “not surprise” him.  “After Bondi and after the explosion of antisemitism in two years of course I am not surprised by hearing such things,” Mr Burnie said.  “It does not surprise me.”

title: ‘Days are numbered’: Pressure mounts on Sussan Ley as Coalition falls apart
description: Sky News host Danica De Giorgio described the Coalition’s split as a “mess”, suggesting Sussan Ley’s position as Opposition Leader is in jeopardy.  “Sussan Ley's days are numbered as Opposition Leader, it seems increasingly likely she will be rolled a week from Tuesday when the Liberal party room meets,” Ms De Giorgio said.   “The Nationals have said see you later, the Liberals are going solo, Sussan Ley is all at sea.   “A new Liberal leader appears to be in the mix, and by all accounts, there's no way the Coalition can rejoin under Sussan Ley.  “It's a mess … the Coalition is split at a time when we so desperately need unity in the wake of Bondi.”

title: Labor’s hate speech laws are ‘contentious’ but a step in the ‘right direction’
description: AJAC Executive Manager Joel Burnie says the hate speech laws were “contentious” but is a step in the right direction”.  “The hate speech laws are contentious, I get that, but the vilification stuff was dropped,” Mr Burnie said.  “The migration changes, the hate groups, and more aggravated penalties for hate preachers, we as the Jewish community think that’s a step in the right direction.”

title: ‘Definition of hypocrisy’: Prince Harry blasted for ‘vendetta’ against British press
description: Sky News host Danica De Giorgio blasts Prince Harry as the “definition of hypocrisy” for continuing his “vendetta” against the press.   “He's been in London … he’s in court as part of his never-ending vendetta against the British press,” Ms De Giorgio said.  “He's suing the papers because he wants privacy, but what qualifies as privacy in his eyes?  “It seems as though the duke of privacy has cashed in on his own privacy one too many times over the years.  “The true definition of hypocrisy.”

title: Greg Moriarty is a ‘very good selection’ for the role of US Ambassador
description: Former Australian major general Mick Ryan says Secretary of the Department of Defence Greg Moriarty is a “very good selection” for the role of US Ambassador.   “Greg is a very good selection as Ambassador, I’ve had the opportunity to work with him in the past,” Mr Ryan told Sky News host Danica De Giorgio.  “He has been part of AUKUS since day one … so I think he’s a fine choice and he’ll do a pretty good job in that appointment.”

title: ‘Ignorant in the extreme’: Trump blasted for ‘repulsive’ Afghanistan war comments
description: Former Australian major general Mick Ryan condemns US President Donald Trump for his “repulsive” comments about the war in Afghanistan.   “They were repulsive comments made by someone who has never served and avoided serving his country,” Mr Ryan told Sky News host Danica De Giorgio.  “They were ignorant in the extreme, and they were wrong.  “These were terrible comments, and I see that he’s already starting to roll them back, at least in the UK.”

title: Nationals and Liberals debate over future of Coalition
description: Sky News host James Macpherson says the “on again, off again” Coalition could be “on again” with a replacement of Sussan Ley.  “The mess that is the Coalition, Nationals Leader David Littleproud has suggested the on again, off again Coalition could be on again,” Mr Macpherson said.  “If the Liberals replace Sussan Ley with the right person.”

title: ‘Magnificent though occasionally malfunctioning’: Australia Day brings mixed reception
description: Sky News host James Macpherson says he will be “celebrating the country” during Australia Day.  “Like most people around this magnificent though occasionally malfunctioning continent I’ll be celebrating it,” Mr Macpherson said.  “A nation so stable that even people who loathe it feel perfectly safe living here while denouncing it.”

title: ABC continues ‘pitting Australians against each other’
description: Sky News host James Macpherson says in the wake of the Bondi terror attack the ABC should “pause briefly in its endless culture war”.  “You’d think the ABC might pause briefly in its endless culture war,” Mr Macpherson said.  “And take seriously its responsibility as the national broadcaster.”

title: Liberal leadership speculation is ‘absolutely forbidden fruit’: Nationals MP
description: Nationals MP Anne Webster discusses the tensions within the Coalition over the recent legislation debacle.  Ms Webster analysed the sacking of three Nationals senators and the potential for reconciliation with the Liberal Party.   She emphasises the Nationals' focus on representing their electorates and suggests a swift reconciliation may not be necessary, while also hinting at the possibility of a change in Liberal leadership.

title: King Charles ‘concerned’ about Donald Trump’s comments on the Afghanistan war
description: TalkTV Host Mark Dolan says US President Donald Trump’s comments about the war in Afghanistan have caused “considerable upset”.   “Even those who admire Donald Trump’s achievements since achieving office are concerned about what he’s had to say,” Mr Dolan told Sky News host James Macpherson.  “Starmer is furious, we understand the King is concerned about it … it’s very awkward diplomatically.”

title: ‘Ultimate nepo baby’: Brooklyn's family rift draws ‘direct parallels’ with Prince Harry
description: TalkTV Host Mark Dolan claims Brooklyn Beckham’s rift with his family draws “direct parallels” with Prince Harry.  “I would say Brooklyn Beckham is an incredibly privileged young man … untold privilege and luxury,” Mr Dolan told Sky News host James Macpherson.  “He’s the ultimate nepo baby, totally entitled, obviously spoiled rotten.  “Direct parallels with Prince Harry … I feel sorry for the Beckhams.”
